entry.title: [sync] Disable data types when related sync policies are lifted
entry.content:
For signed-in non-syncing users with kReplaceSyncPromosWithSignInPromos

enabled, the expected behaviour when SyncDisabled, or

SyncTypesListDisabled is lifted is to have the types that were affected

by the policy toggled off.

This is not the current case, where affected types become enabled after

lifting the policies.



This CL updates the current behaviour to match the expected, by

introducing SyncPrefsPolicyHandler class which disables the affected

types when the policy is active.



The policies, SyncDisabled and SyncTypesListDisabled support "Dynamic

Policy Refresh"; for SyncPrefsPolicyHandler to work as expected in this

case, it observes SyncServiceObserver.



Note: manual testing of policy dynamic changes is not possible using

experiment settings, for iOS, it is only possible using egtests.



Fixed: 40068922

entry.title: win: Use -O3 in optimize_speed
entry.content:
Pass /clang:-O3 after /O2 in the "optimize_speed" config. This increases

the optimization level for targets in this config from -O2 to -O3 on

Windows.



"/O2" means something slightly different for clang-cl than

"-O2" means for clang!



For clang-cl, "/O2" is short for "/Og /Oi /Ot /Oy /Ob2 /GF /Gy".

"/Ot" is "optimize for speed" and means the same as "-O2" for

clang. The other flags turn on things like -ffunction-sections.



Non-clang-cl clang's -O3 isn't exposed in the clang-cl driver.

But we can use the `/clang:` flag to pass it through.



(See TranslateOptArg() in MSVC.cpp and

CLModePassThroughArgList in Driver.cpp in clang/lib/Driver)

Experimenting with `clang-cl /O2 /clang:-O3 -###` also suggests

that this should do the right thing.)

entry.content:
The issue in b/306223405 is caused by ClipboardOzone having an async

clipboard, meaning the `GetSequenceNumber` call in

`ClipboardHostImpl::CommitWrite` won't return the correct value as

it is called synchronously before ClipboardOzone has finished writing

data and has a new seqno. Since that value is later checked in

`PasteIfPolicyAllowed`, Linux was the only platform to not be

scan-exempt when copy-pasting withing the same tab.



This CL fixes the issue by updating the last copied seqno through a

`ui::ClipboardObserver` instead of a sync call. This also fixes other

source-tracking issues on Linux observed in Data Controls (b/324881200).



Fixed: 306223405, 324881200

entry.title: Propagate AudioGlitchInfo to MediaStreamAudioTrack::OnData()
entry.content:
This CL propagates the AudioGlitchInfo provided by AudioInputDevices

to MediaStreams. The purpose is to plumb it all the way to

MediaStreamAudioTrack::OnData(), which is a part of the plan to

implement the MediaStreamTrackAudioStats API. For the full plan, see

go/mediastream-audio-stats-implementation.



The flow of the glitch info introduced in this CL looks like this:

AudioInputDevice (this step was done in the previous CL) ->

(LocalMediaStreamAudioSource/ProcessedLocalAudioSource)::Capture() ->

MediaStreamAudioSource::DeliverDataToTracks() ->

MediaStreamAudioDeliverer::OnData() ->

->

MediaStreamAudioTrack::OnData()



Most of the changes are just updating function signatures. The

functional changes are in the following files:

* local_media_stream_audio_source.cc

* processed_local_audio_source.cc

* media_stream_audio_source.cc

* media_stream_audio_deliverer.h

also an specific argument for that purpose.

is because we cannot accurately know if libstdc++ is used, so we want

entry.title: Fix ColorSpace issue for DrawVideoFrameIntoResourceProvider()
entry.content:
GPUExternalTexture uses a opt uploading path CopyVideoFrameToSharedImage() to achieve 1-copy path. DrawVideoFrameIntoResourceProvider() was added in CL

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/5329940

as a fallback path.



However there are some remain issues:

- The check about using CopyVideoFrameToSharedImage() is not restricted.

- The color space issue in DrawVideoFrameIntoResourceProvider(),

mentioned in crbug.com/1407112 was not workaround.



This CL fixed above issues by correcting checking condition about using

CopyVideoFrameToSharedImage() and working around color space issue for

DrawVideoFrameIntoResourceProvider() path.
